Class RGBSelect

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • javax.swing.JComponent
          • javax.swing.JPanel
            • gui.elements.RGBSelect
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, java.util.EventListener, javax.accessibility.Accessible

    public class RGBSelect
extends javax.swing.JPanel
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener
    A Panel that enables the user to select three features and add a rgb view to the ExtraFrame visualization.

    Each one of the selected features will be used for ine color channel. I guess, this may look nice

    The used ExtraFrame instance, as well as the DataMatrix that provides the features may be changed at runtime. In this case, the labels and the dropboxes change automatically.

    If one tries to add a view when the Visualization is null, an Error Dialog is shown.

    Author:
    pwelke
